data <- read.csv("mobilePhoneData.csv")

Mydata<- data.frame(t(data[-1]))
colnames(Mydata) <- data[, 1]

Mydata$dual_sim[Mydata$dual_sim==""] <- NA

Mydata$dual_sim <-factor(Mydata$dual_sim)
Mydata$dual_sim<-as.integer(Mydata$dual_sim)

Mydata$wifi <- factor(Mydata$wifi)
Mydata$wifi <- as.integer(Mydata$wifi)

data <- read.csv("mobilePhoneData.csv")

Mydata$dual_sim <-factor(Mydata$dual_sim)
Mydata$dual_sim<-as.integer(Mydata$dual_sim)

Mydata$wifi <- factor(Mydata$wifi)
Mydata$wifi <- as.integer(Mydata$wifi)


Mydata$three_g <- factor(Mydata$three_g)
Mydata$three_g <- as.integer(Mydata$three_g)

Mydata <- mutate_if(Mydata,is.character,as.numeric)

str(Mydata)

sum(!complete.cases(Mydata))
data.clean = na.omit(Mydata)
data.clean

data.clean$battery_power <- Catagorical

PieData <- table(data.clean$n_cores)
PieData <- as.data.frame(PieData)
n_coresDF <- PieData
colnames(n_coresDF) <- c("NumberOfCores", "Count")
percentlabels <- round(100 * n_coresDF$Count / sum(n_coresDF$Count))
pielabels<- paste(percentlabels, "%", sep="")
ggplot(data = n_coresDF, aes(x = NumberOfCores, y = Count, fill = NumberOfCores)) + 
geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
geom_text(aes(label = pielabels), position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5)) +
labs(fill = 'Type', x = NULL, y = NULL, title = 'Number Of Cores', subtitle = 'in perventages') +
coord_polar(theta = "y") +
theme_minimal()

data <- read.csv("Householddata.csv",header = TRUE)
# Yes There Missing data as we can seen in summary ,I will be removing the missing data
names(data)


df<- subset(data, select = -c(X,Education.Level.1,X.1,X.2,GHH..Gender.of.the.Household.Head,X.3))
str(df)
summary(df)
sum(!complete.cases(df))

df[df==" "]<-NA
df[df==""]<-NA

df<-na.omit(df)
sapply(df, function(x) sum(is.na(x)))
# Normalization is required 

df$Income <-  type.convert(df$Income)

df$TotalExpendecture <- (df$Groceries + df$Meals + df$Utilities + df$Cloth +df$Alcohol + df$Fuel + df$Phone)

Income_scale_T<-(df$Taxes - mean(df$Taxes)) / sd (df$Taxes)

df$Taxes<-Income_scale_T

Income_scale_E<-(df$TotalExpendecture - mean(df$TotalExpendecture)) / sd (df$TotalExpendecture)

df$TotalExpendecture<-Income_scale_E
df
#ggplot(data = df, mapping = aes(x =Income, y =TotalExpendecture)) + geom_density(color="darkblue", fill="#FF6666") 
datadf <- df[1:10,]
p1 <- ggplot(data = datadf, mapping = aes(x =Income, y =TotalExpendecture)) +geom_boxplot()+coord_flip()

p2 <- ggplot(data = datadf, mapping = aes(x = Income, y = Taxes,
fill=Income)) +
geom_boxplot() +coord_flip()

ggarrange(p1, p2, ncol = 2, nrow = 1)
